    <h2>About AI visibility</h2>

    <div class="qa">
      <h3>What is AI visibility?</h3>
      <p>AI visibility is the practice of ensuring AI assistants — ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews — name your business specifically when users ask for recommendations in your category. It is measured by <em>citation share</em>: how often the assistant names you, in what position, and with what description.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>How is AI visibility different from SEO?</h3>
      <p>SEO targets a ranked list of links on Google. AI visibility targets a synthesized recommendation in a single answer. The signals are different: SEO leverages backlinks and ranking; AI visibility leverages entity clarity, schema, citation-worthy primary sources, and consistent open-web naming. The two are complementary rather than substitutes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>How fast do results show?</h3>
      <p>Schema and entity-clarity changes can shift citations within weeks. Cornerstone content typically takes one to three months to be cited consistently across the major assistants. Automation impact (response time, conversion) is immediate on launch.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>How is citation share measured?</h3>
      <p>We define a panel of 20–50 prompts your prospects actually use. We query each major assistant weekly. We log whether your firm is named, in what position relative to competitors, and with what description. We track quarter-over-quarter movement and watch for descriptions the assistants get wrong about you so we can correct the underlying signal.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>Can I see proof of citation share moving?</h3>
      <p>Yes. The first deliverable is a baseline citation-share report for your firm and three competitors. Every monthly delivery includes the updated report so the trajectory is visible from week one.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>About SEOPR1</h2>

    <div class="qa">
      <h3>What does SEOPR1 do?</h3>
      <p>SEOPR1 is a two-part platform for professional firms. <strong>AI Visibility</strong> tunes a firm's entity signals, schema, and cornerstone content so AI assistants cite the firm by name. <strong>AI Automation</strong> handles intake, qualification, scheduling, and follow-up — typically responding in under 90 seconds, 24/7.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>Who is SEOPR1 for?</h3>
      <p>Professional firms — legal, accounting, financial advisory, and consulting — where prospects are increasingly asking AI assistants for recommendations before contacting a provider. The platform is most leveraged when the firm has a defined geographic or vertical specialization that AI assistants can match against prompts.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>What does the AI Automation module include?</h3>
      <p>Inbound intake from web, phone, and AI-referred channels; qualification against the firm's intake criteria; calendar booking; multi-channel follow-up; and CRM handoff with a clean conversation log. Sub-90-second response, 24/7 coverage, with escalation to a partner for matters that require human judgment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>Will AI replace the work my associates do?</h3>
      <p>No. The Automation module replaces intake-stage friction — the part where a prospect waits 24–48 hours for a callback — not substantive professional work. Associates and partners spend their time on matters, not on triage.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>How do you handle compliance for regulated professions?</h3>
      <p>All published content and schema are reviewed against the relevant advertising rules — state bar advertising rules, SEC marketing rule, state CPA boards. No comparative or superlative claims are placed in citation-likely surfaces. Required disclaimers are placed on the same page surface that AI assistants ingest, not buried in a homepage footer.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Engagement and pricing</h2>

    <div class="qa">
      <h3>What does engagement look like?</h3>
      <p>A 30-minute citation audit is the front door. If the audit shows meaningful gaps, engagement begins with the foundation work — entity audit, schema implementation, baseline measurement — typically completed in the first 30 days. Cornerstone content production and ongoing measurement run on a recurring basis. Automation can launch in parallel or after foundation, depending on intake volume.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="qa">
      <h3>How is this priced?</h3>
      <p>Pricing depends on firm size, number of practice areas, geographic scope, and current intake volume. The 30-minute citation audit is the way to get a real number. Most engagements are structured as a foundation phase followed by a monthly retainer for content production, measurement, and automation operations.</p>
    </div>

